events.name: GDG (Google Developer Group) Introduction Meeting + Call for Volunteers

group.name: Google Developers Group - GDG West Sweden

events.description:
GDG (Google Developer Group) Introduction Meeting + Call for Volunteers + Strategy and Planning
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GDG stands for Google Developers Groups and is a platform offered by Google Developers to support community-run developer groups.

Volunteering / Speaking / Hosting Application links are listed below.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Welcome to the Official GDG West Sweden Meetup Group

Mission Statement: To translate technology awareness into actionable learning for personal and professional growth.

If you need more information then please directly reach out to: [masked]

About GDG West Sweden

We are a technology-based group that is completely run by a community of volunteer organizers. Because of this we are always looking for volunteer help in running events, and are open to community suggestions and contributions in terms of speakers, event venues and sponsorships.

The primary goal is to create actionable networking, collaboration and entrepreneurial connections for technology enthusiasts in West Sweden.

We welcome all the software developers, analysts, designers, and students with an interest in learning about emergent technologies in areas including (but not limited to) AI, Machine Learning, mobile, web, wearables, cloud computing, robotics, data sciences, and smart homes.

Events can vary from featured Tech Talks (40 mins or more) to Short Talks (20 mins), Lightning Talks (5 mins) as well as focused ones like workshops, hackathons, study jams.

Our talks may feature Google technology (e.g., Chrome, Android, AngularJS, Google Glass, Android Wear, Polymer, Google Compute Engine, etc.) but also extends to competitive technologies, products, and platforms.

Members

Please make sure your profile is updated with your full name. This is often required by our hosts as they need to create a valid guest list

Speakers

We're always looking for new speakers, everyone is welcome. Please fill in this form and we'll get back to you as soon as we can: https://forms.gle/wCqTQooCcg44bKJn8

Hosts

We're also looking for hosts to sponsor our meetups. If you want to sponsor a meetup, please fill out this form: https://forms.gle/5Hmin7D3j6v3HWhA8

Volunteering

Want to volunteer to help at any of our events? Sign up here: https://forms.gle/N3pW1FyUjnNsTio49

CODE OF CONDUCT

All members of the GDG West Sweden are expected to adhere to our Code of Conduct. Simply put: "Be Excellent to each other". Harassment of any kind (physical, verbal, digital) will not be tolerated and can potentially lead to expulsion from events, or even from the community. A more detailed version of the Code of Conduct is found here: https://tinyurl.com/CCGDGGBG

Disclaimer: GDG West Sweden is an independent group; our activities and the opinions expressed here should in no way be linked to Google, the corporation. To learn more about the GDG program, visit https://developers.google.com/groups/

events.name: Google Assistant From Scratch With Dialogflow | GDG West Sweden

group.name: Google Developers Group - GDG West Sweden

events.description:
The GDG West Sweden is starting 2020 with a new event focused on DialogFlow -"Google Assistant from scratch" conducted by Valon Huskaj. The event will take place at Squeed AB (Packhusplatsen 2 · Göteborg) on January 16th, 2020 from 17:30 to 19:30

------

After the demos, we will gather for a cozy Q&A/Networking session around Technology and Google products where our organizers and mentors will be happy to answer your questions and chat more!

Don't forget to bring your laptops if you would like to follow the demos step by step and build your own prototypes.

Our team can't wait to see you all and welcome newcomers to our vibrant community! It's also a great opportunity to meet with Swapnil who recently joined the organizer's team.

Join our Discord to meet the community online as well and continue the chat!

-------

We would like you all to make the following preparation to get out as much as possible form the session.

Required

Install NodeJS, v8 or later.
Create a Google Account if don’t already have one.

Optional 1

If you would like to use Cloud Functions, make sure you can login to the console on the Google Cloud Platform.

Optional 2

If you would like to use the integration with Västtrafik later on your own devices I would recommend you to create an account at: https://developer.vasttrafik.se/

See you soon,
The GDG West Sweden Organisers

events.name: Hash Code 2020 - Google's Coding Competitions -GDG West Sweden | IAESTE Göteborg

group.name: Google Developers Group - GDG West Sweden

events.description:
HURRY UP: Are you up for the challenge? Register by February 16! : https://codingcompetitions.withgoogle.com/hashcode

What is Hash Code?

Google’s team-based programming competition, Hash Code, allows you to share your skills and connect with other coders as you work together to solve a problem modeled off a real Google engineering challenge! In small teams of two to four, coders all over the world will tackle the first problem through an Online Qualification Round.
Teams come together to compete side-by-side in locally coordinated Hash Code hubs. The top teams from this round are invited to join us at an international Google office for our annual Hash Code Final Round.

Problems are modeled on Google engineering challenges. Past problems have included perfecting video streaming on YouTube and optimizing the layout of a Google data center: https://codingcompetitions.withgoogle.com/hashcode/archive

You can compete with your friends. You need to form a team of 2 to 4 people to compete in Hash Code. If you don’t have a team, don’t worry! Come to the venue, you may create your own team then and there itself. Or find teammates later using our Facebook group: https://www.facebook.com/groups/GoogleHashCode/

The World Finals will be hosted at Google Ireland. Top teams from the Online Qualification Round will be invited to Dublin in April to compete for cash prizes and the title of Hash Code 2020 Champion.

Make sure you don't miss out on the action by first creating a Coding Competitions profile for 2020, and then registering for Hash Code 2020. You can always check the Schedule page to confirm you've successfully registered: https://codingcompetitions.withgoogle.com/hashcode/schedule

For any queries please reach out to us : Prajit: [masked] / [masked]

events.name: Machine Learning Research Journal Hours | GDG West Sweden | Supported by AFRY

group.name: Google Developers Group - GDG West Sweden

events.description:
Hello Everyone,
Its a regular meetup event, where we will meet to critically evaluate recent research articles being published in the field of Machine Learning. These journal hours will be curated and hosted by Dr. Sven-Patrik Hallsjö.

For the journal hour, we'll discuss the following paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/1412.6572
This is an early research article from google discussing adversarial examples.
I am hoping to discuss the following points:
Is this good research?
What was the point of the article?
Could you understand and reproduce the results?
Would you have changed something in the article? If so what?
How does this relate to what you have seen today?

My role will be to start of the discussions and to moderate them, ensuring we stay on track

-----------------------------------------------------

TF Developer Certification: https://www.tensorflow.org/certificate

TF Candidate Handbook: https://www.tensorflow.org/site-assets/downloads/marketing/cert/TF_Certificate_Candidate_Handbook.pdf

TensorFlow Developer Certificate program overview
-------------------------------------
The goal of this certificate is to provide everyone in the world the opportunity to showcase their expertise in ML in an increasingly AI-driven global job market. This certificate in TensorFlow development is intended as a foundational certificate for students, developers, and data scientists who want to demonstrate practical machine learning skills through the building and training of models using TensorFlow.

The program consists of an assessment exam developed by the TensorFlow team. Developers who pass the exam can join our Certificate Network and display their certificate and badges on their resume, GitHub, and social media platforms including LinkedIn, making it easy to share their level of TensorFlow expertise with the world.

Who is the TensorFlow Certificate for?
-----------------------------------
This level one certificate exam tests a developers foundational knowledge of integrating machine learning into tools and applications. The certificate program requires an understanding of building TensorFlow models using Computer Vision, Convolutional Neural Networks, Natural Language Processing, and real-world image data and strategies.

In order to successfully take the exam, test takers should be comfortable with:

a) Foundational principles of ML and Deep Learning
b) Building ML models in TensorFlow
c) Building image recognition, object detection, text recognition algorithms with deep neural networks and convolutional neural networks
d) Using real-world images in different shapes and sizes to visualize the journey of an image through convolutions to understand how a computer “sees” information, plot loss and accuracy
e) Exploring strategies to prevent overfitting, including augmentation and dropouts
f) Applying neural networks to solve natural language processing problems using TensorFlow

Benefits
----------
a) Learn something new. Increase your proficiency in machine learning, and test your abilities with the TensorFlow assessment exam.
b) Receive community recognition. Be recognized by others in the global TensorFlow community.
c) Showcase your skills. Share your certificate on your resume and social networking platforms like LinkedIn to be recognized as a top candidate for recruiters seeking entry-level TensorFlow developers.
d) Find TensorFlow talent. See who is a certificate holder in our Certificate Network, and find help for your machine learning tasks.

TF Certificate Network: https://www.tensorflow.org/certificate-network

For more information, please reach out to [masked] / [masked]

Google Developers Group - GDG West Sweden is proud to join hands with Hack for Sweden and openhack - coding for humanity to organize a digital hackathon 'Hack the Crisis'. This initiative is backed by Swedish Government and other partners such as DIGG – Myndigheten för digital förvaltning Gothenburg Tech Week Volvo Cars ZENUITY The Techno Creatives and Göteborg & Co

The focus will be on three main tracks of challenges:
- Save lives
- Save communities
- Save businesses

The mission is to design, test and execute ideas for the future of Sweden and the world. We want to gather creative ideas and develop concepts in an attempt to create solutions helping us make further progress in the ongoing resistance.

Join us for our Building AMP Stories - Online Workshop - by Vrijraj Singh from GDG Jalandhar.

Agenda
1. What's is AMP & AMP Stories (30min)
2. AMP Stories Workshop (60-90 min)

AMP (Accelerated Mobile Pages) is an open-source HTML framework created by Google that provides a straightforward way to create web pages that are fast, smooth-loading and prioritize the user-experience above all else.

AMP Stories
Visual storytelling for the open web

AMP stories immerse your readers in fast-loading full-screen experiences. Easily create visual narratives, with engaging animations and tappable interactions. The AMP story format is free and part of the open web and is available for everyone to try on their websites. They can be shared and embedded across the web without being confined to a closed ecosystem or platform.

AMP stories provide content publishers with a mobile-focused format for delivering news and information as visually rich, tap-through stories. AMP Stories offers a robust set of advertising opportunities for advertisers and publishers to reach a unique audience on the web with immersive experiences.

Join us for our Get started with Cloud Computing - Online Workshop - by Sachin Sadasivan - GDG Athlone, Ireland

As cloud computing slowly continues to replace traditional software infrastructure, many enterprises are still grappling with the best route forward, ramping up the talent and know-how to leverage all of the new technology emerging from the big cloud vendors, all while keeping their businesses up and running.

Agenda
• Cloud Computing - What and why?
• Google Cloud Platform
• Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Overview
○ GCP resources
○ Accessing resources through services
○ Global, regional, and zonal resources
○ Projects
○ Ways to interact with the services
§ Google Cloud Console
§ Command-line interface
§ Client libraries
○ Pricing
• Creating a Google Cloud Account
• GCP services
○ Compute/ Processing Services
○ Storage Services
○ Networking Services
• Understanding GCP Compute/ Processing Services

○ Hands on lab : Creating and Editing a VM Instance
Prerequisites:

events.name: [ONLINE] AMP Study Jam - Web Development Beginning Course with Ben Morss, Google

group.name: Google Developers Group - GDG West Sweden

events.description:
Register in advance for this meeting:
https://us02web.zoom.us/meeting/register/tZMrceGqqzkpH9Egx44abO8sVwiCjgu6nYEs

After registering, you will receive a confirmation email containing information about joining the meeting.
--------------------

AMP is an open-source HTML framework created by Google that provides a straightforward way to create web pages that are fast, smooth-loading and prioritize the user-experience above all else.

Want to get started on building AMP websites? Join us for our AMP Study Jam! Together we'll work through the "Web Development with AMP - Beginning Course" prepared and led by our instructor Ben Morss from Google.

Discuss on Slack:
https://gdgnordic.herokuapp.com/

WHAT YOU'LL LEARN
You will be able to get hands-on experience with AMP and build an AMP website while learning the fundamentals. We recommend that you follow the code with the online editor Glitch. The course starts here:
https://glitch.com/~showy-way

WHAT YOU'LL NEED:
Your own PC, Mac or Chromebook with a good internet connection to join Google Hangouts Meet to watch and Slack to discuss.

AGENDA:
5:30 pm - Join group call and intro
5:40 pm - Web Development with AMP - Beginning Course Workshop (https://glitch.com/~showy-way) with Ben Morss, Google
7:40 pm - Questions and Answers
8:00 pm - Wrap up

INSTRUCTOR BIO:
Ben Morss is a Developer Advocate at Google, where he’s working to help the Web be faster and more beautiful. Prior to Google, he worked at the New York Times and AOL, and before that he was a full-time musician. He earned a BA in Computer Science at Harvard and a PhD in Music at the University of California. Rumor is that he still runs a band called Ancient Babies.

No presentations, no planned agenda. Let’s just meet and talk!

This is an invitation to a very simple after-work mingle. We’ll get some drinks and discuss everything that we do not have time to talk about before or after the meetups. This is a great opportunity to actually hang out with peers of the same interests, share thoughts, and celebrate the season!

We’ll meet at Scandic Rubinen’s bar. The bar is at the bottom floor and opens at 17:30. Look out for people wearing "Google" Tshirts. You’re welcome to come and go as you want. The event is not sponsored, so food and drinks are at your own expense, but there’s plenty of alternatives in the bar if you get thirsty or want to grab some snacks.

Hope to see you there!

Registration Link: https://forms.gle/r3ZWun3cMygjw3Ja9

Join us for our upcoming Machine Learning Bootcamp (Cloud Study Jam)- Sponsored by AFRY and get hands-on experience with TensorFlow and GCP.

Top 5 reasons to attend a Study Jam: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FvWl7Ftz1uM

We will cover one of these topics TBD:
- Baseline: Data, ML, AI
- Language Processing Study Jam
- Image Processing Study Jam
- Tensorflow on GCP Study Jam
- ML Infrastructure Study Jam
- Machine Learning APIs

You’ll Receive:
Free access to Qwiklabs hands-on labs, a $55+ value
Earn Google Cloud badges to show your skills and expertise
No need to register with a credit card

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Food? Yes!!!!

upcoming.description:
Join us for our Flutter Study Jam (For Beginners) by GDG West Sweden - Google Developers Groups! - Mentored by Sahil Lakhe

Flutter is Google’s portable UI kit for crafting high-quality native interfaces on iOS and Android in record time. Flutter works with existing code, is used by developers and organizations around the world, and is free and open source.

Together we'll work through Flutter codelabs prepared by Google instructors. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Flutter and build an app while learning the fundamentals.

You will meet like-minded, passionate people, network and produce some code!

IMPORTANT INFO:
Bring a laptop! For the best experience, the laptop should have Flutter installed on it prior to starting the study jam to save time. Windows/Linux/Mac would all be fine.

Please check if after installing Flutter SDK your laptop can compile and run a basic empty app in Flutter.

Check out: https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install

Please install Visual Studio Code if you don't have Android Studio already set up
How to install VsCode: https://flutter.dev/docs/development/tools/vs-code

Windows setup: https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install/windows
Mac setup: https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install/macos
Linux setup: https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install/linux

We will go through both theory and practical examples with some live coding, so developers of all levels should find something useful for them.

This event is being held in collaboration with DevPort AB.
